node.title: Homicide investigation underway after man, 22, dies in Auckland
node.description: The man was dropped off at a Takanini medical centre about 12.45pm with critical injuries and was taken to Middlemore Hospital where he died shortly after.

node.title: Borders set to reopen, but vaccination rates still flagging in poorer and multicultural communities
node.description: As several states get set to welcome incoming travellers when border restrictions are repealed, vaccination disparity remains a problem, with public health experts concerned that some disadvantaged, Aboriginal and multicultural communities are unprepared.

node.title: Investors say new WA bill won't prevent another Juukan Gorge scandal
node.description: Investors have teamed up with Indigenous leaders in Western Australia to push for changes a new bill designed to prevent the destruction of Aboriginal sacred sites.
